# Evidence and scanner safety

- Evidence upload, attachment, linking and review do not equal verification.
- Malware scanning concerns attachment safety only.
- Scanner work must not silently alter claim support or verification status.
- Review requests remain private and are not certification.
- Require owner scoping for user-owned rows.
- Preserve hash snapshot and stale-work guards.
- Do not introduce file reads, subprocesses, network calls, OCR, parsing or LLM review unless the named phase explicitly approves them.
- Do not introduce worker loops, startup registration, quarantine, audit, admin routes or frontend scan UI outside the approved phase.
- Record exact allowed model fields and state transitions.
- Require idempotency and atomicity analysis before result persistence.
